18/10/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Two opposition parties -- the Power of Serbia Movement (PSS) headed by Bogoljub Karic and the Social Democratic Party (SDP) headed by Nebojsa Covic -- sealed an agreement on co-operation Monday (17 October).
They said they intend to jointly seek early parliamentary elections in the republic.
SDP, which recently left the Serbian ruling coalition after a political scandal among the coalition partners, currently has two deputies in parliament.
PSS has one.
Karic and Covic stressed that their parties are open to collaboration with others interested in early elections.
(Beta, Tanjug - 17/10/05)
